Unit tests in JavaScript are a type of testing where individual units or components of a program are tested in
isolation to ensure that they function correctly.

The goal is to validate that each unit of code (typically functions or methods) performs as expected

// math.js

function add(a, b) {
return a + b;
}

module.exports = add;

// math.test.js

const add = require('./math');

test('adds 1 + 2 to equal 3', () => {
expect(add(1, 2)).toBe(3);
});



//Command for installation 

